					<dd class="comment byuser comment-author-wbrounds bypostauthor odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-287">
<p>I am not really aware of any established hawala networks working over the internet offering formal accounts.  There are of course informal hawala transactions occurring all the time.   Part of the problem may be the requirement for hawaladars to register with the federal government to carry on hawala transactions as a business in the US.   Another problem is the informal nature of hawala networks means they rarely advertise their services.  You might try looking in some of the communities where hawala transactions are common to see if you can be introduced to people who can help you.  Those communities might be an immigrant community, or communities from the place where you want to send money.</p>
</div>
